AU  - Andreasen, Martin M
AU  - Engsted, Tom
AU  - Møller, Stig V
AU  - Sander, Magnus
T1  - The Yield Spread and Bond Return Predictability in Expansions and Recessions
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa107
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 6
SP  - 2773
EP  - 2812
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper uncovers that expected excess bond returns display a positive correlation with the slope of the yield curve (i.e., yield spread) in expansions but a negative correlation in recessions. We use a macro-finance term structure model with different market prices of risk in expansions and recessions to show that a very accommodating monetary policy in recessions is a key driver of this switch in return predictability.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa107
ER  - 



