T1  - Risks and Returns of Cryptocurrency
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa113
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 6
SP  - 2689
EP  - 2727
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We establish that cryptocurrency returns are driven and can be predicted by factors that are specific to cryptocurrency markets. Cryptocurrency returns are exposed to cryptocurrency network factors but not cryptocurrency production factors. We construct the network factors to capture the user adoption of cryptocurrencies and the production factors to proxy for the costs of cryptocurrency production. Moreover, there is a strong time-series momentum effect, and proxies for investor attention strongly forecast future cryptocurrency returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa113
ER  - 



